69.15: The Curtain Call is also by—
69.20: I'm not Skipping Class, I'm on a Mission!
69.84: An Amount fit for her Daughter
69.8001: If you're not going fast during the last spurt, you might be lacking speed.
69.8002: If you're losing positions in the final stretch, you might be lacking stamina.
69.8003: If you find yourself unable to get ahead, it might be good to increase your power.
69.8004: If you find yourself unable to catch up in the final stretch, you might be lacking guts.
69.8005: With higher wisdom, positioning and skill activation becomes easier.
69.8006: If you're low on Money and Support Points, try entering the Daily Races.
69.8007: Upgrading your Support Cards and Umamusume is key to winning races.
69.8008: Race outcomes are not only decided by what happens during the race, but also the weather and sometimes even luck...
69.8009: Upgrading the level of your Support Cards will give you better support effects.
69.8010: Limit Breaking your Support Cards will give you powerful support effects.
69.8011: The effect [Motivation Bonus] also amplifies negative effects, so be careful!
69.8012: The effect [Friendship Bonus] increases the effect of Friendship Training.
69.8013: The [Parameter Bonus] effects increase the results of a specific training.
69.8014: The [Training Bonus] effect increases the results of any training.
69.8015: The [Initial Parameter Bonus] effects increase stats at the start of training.
69.8016: I recommend the [Initial Bond Gauge Bonus] effect if you want to max bond gauges quickly.
69.8017: [Race Bonus] and [Fan Count Bonus] also affect goal races.
69.8018: I recommend the [Race Bonus] effect if you want to earn more Skill Points.
69.8019: The [Hint Level Bonus] effect lets you increase Hint levels more quickly.
69.8020: The [Hint Chance Bonus] effect increases the chance of a Hint showing up.
69.8021: The [Specialty Rate Up] effect increases the chance of a support character appearing on their training type.
69.8022: The [Event Recovery Up] effect increases the energy recovered during events.
69.8023: The [Event Effect Up] effect increases the results of events.
69.8024: The [Failure Rate Down] effect makes it less likely to fail when training with the support character.
69.8025: The [Energy Discount] effect reduces the energy consumed when training with the support character.
69.8026: The [Wisdom Training Recovery Up] effect increases the energy recovered when doing Friendship Wisdom Training.
69.8027: Friendship Trainings will occur after the bond gauge turns orange.
69.8028: When multiple Friendship Trainings occur at once, the effects will be even greater.
69.8029: Events of equipped Support Cards are much more likely to occur.
69.8030: You may sometimes get events from unequipped Support Cards, too!
69.8031: Note: You cannot equip Support Cards of the same Umamusume you are training.
69.8032: You can convert unwanted Support Cards into Horseshoes, which can be exchanged for items in the Shop.
69.8033: You can check the Skill Hints you can get from Support Cards in the [Training Events] section of the details page.
69.8034: You can increase the Awakening level of trainable Umamusume with items and Money.
69.8035: The higher the Awakening level, the more skills you start a training with.
69.8036: You can obtain items for Awakening by winning races of G3 or higher during training.
69.8037: You can upgrade Umamusume by collecting their pieces.
69.9133: She has a peculiar way of naming things.
69.9193: She loves to share food with others.
69.9194: Prefers to take local trains over express trains (because there are always open seats.)
69.9196: She has a habit of lazing around outside of training. She ends up getting scolded by her mentor for it.
69.9197: She gets a cold easily, so she wears thick fluffy clothes at home.
69.9198: She never loses a palm pushing match.

88.10001: My name is Special Week! My dream is to be the best horse girl in Japan! I'm gonna pull my own weight to make my moms proud!
88.10002: I'm Silence Suzuka. I like to run. I'm not giving the lead to anyone. Um... That's all.
88.10003: Heya, I'm Tokai Teio! I'm going to be an undefeated Triple Crown horse girl, so don't let me out of your sight!
88.10004: Hi, I'm Maruzensky! Did you come to see this new style of running too? Hehe ♪ Even though I'm crazy about it... I don't know how to feel ♪
88.10005: I am Oguri Cap. I'm going to do my best to make everyone in my hometown happy. Please take care of me.
88.10006: Yo, I'm Gold Ship! I don't care if it's on the turf, on fire, or at the edge of the universe. I'm going to find something interesting wherever I can! ☆
88.10007: Yo, I'm Vodka! My goal is to be the coolest horse girl in the world! I'm not gonna do anything stupid. Remember that!
88.10008: Howdy! I'm Taiki Shuttle! I'm here to make everyone happy with my powerful running!
88.10009: My name is Grass Wonder. Since I was born as a horse girl, I want to pursue this path to the end. Hehe ♪
88.10010: My name is Mejiro McQueen. Conquering the "Spring Tennosho" has been a long-cherished goal of the Mejiro family, and I will do it with my own two legs.
88.10011: I'm the crimson bird that runs the course! El Condor Pasa is closing in! I'm flying around the world!
88.10012: Haa-ha-ha-ha! I am the strongest and most beautiful of them all, the "Supreme King", T.M. Opera O! Now, let the legend begin!
88.10013: I am Symboli Rudolf. I am the one who will stand at the top of every horse girl and lead them to become "Emperors". Those of you who share my aspirations, let's work together to conquer the world!
88.10014: Yahoo-, it's Seiun Sky. Take your time and relax... When you're aiming for a big goal, it's important to take your time, right?
88.10015: I'm... Rice Shower. Um... I'm a useless girl who makes others unhappy... but I'm trying my best to change!
88.10016: My... My... My dream is to be a Derby horse girl! And then there's... ah! My name!!!! My name is Winning Ticket! Nice to meet you!
88.10017: Gold City. ...Just so you know, I won't forgive you if you treat me like a doll. Don't judge me by my looks, but by the way I run.
88.10018: Hello! My name is Sakura Bakushin O! As you can see, I am a brilliant class representative! Let's set a great example for everyone! BAKUSHIIIN!
88.10019: Tee-hee... I'm Super Creek~ I'll do my best to make everyone smile. Please leave it to me ♪
88.10020: I'm Haru Urara! I love carrots and I lo~ve running because it's fun!♪ I'm going to try my very best to finish first!
88.10021: Hello, I am Tazuna Hayakawa, secretary to the president of Tracen Academy. I will continue to support you so that you can have a better school life.
88.10022: Hello, I am Aoi Kiryuin. I'm a new trainer at Tracen Academy. I'm still a novice, but I'll do my best for the sake of the horse girls!
88.10023: Hello, I'm Daiwa Scarlet! I'll do my best to... Hmph! I'm going to be number one. That's all!
88.10025: I am Air Groove. If you don't bend your beliefs, your ideals will surely sprout. To demonstrate this, I, the Empress, will be the guiding light for everyone.
88.10026: Hewwo! I'm Digi-tan! I'm a massive fan of all of the sparkling horse girls! I'm so happy every day! I'm so glad I was born an otaku!~♪
88.10027: Ah'm Tamamo Cross! A'hm gonna win'n win'n win to make a name for myself! Don't underestimate me just 'cause ah'm small!
88.10029: I'm Biwa Hayahide. My goal is to assemble the perfect winning formula. ...Also, I have a normal-sized head!
